 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Recruiter - Remote US Seamless.AI 9 reviews Columbus, OH Remote Seamless.AI 9 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Opportunity 
The Recruiter is responsible for supporting and working alongside the Talent Acquisition Team by proactively sourcing talent, reviewing applications, building relationships and executing creative and innovative sourcing strategies. The successful candidate must have a strong understanding of the marketplace and possess the ability to review applications and pre-screen large quantities of candidates on availability, interest level, salary range, and qualifications. They will also partner with the Talent Acquisition Manager to generate ideas, leverage resources and share information to drive business success in a growing organization. 
 
 
Recruiter Responsibilities Include:
 Develop and execute innovative search techniques to generate abundant applicant pools. 
Must be able to cold call and build relationships by phone/email using job boards and social media sites to generate awareness and candidate flow; all while providing appropriate candidate follow up. 
Determine new/creative ways to introduce Seamless.AI to potential active and passive candidates. 
Participate in advancing candidates forward by conducting and scheduling candidate interviews. 
Act as a search expert for various functional areas by understanding hiring needs, position specifications and search requirements. 
Perform extensive Internet based research, cold calling and other sourcing techniques to introduce the best candidates and build future pipelines. 
Ensure all required documentation is completed for all candidates throughout the sourcing process. 
Manage and network with employee referrals. 
Participate and help plan company specific hiring events and attend job fairs as needed. 
Participate in ad-hoc projects, other duties, and future assignments as required. 
 Qualifications: 
1+ years of full-cycle recruiting experience including but not limited to sourcing for talent, conducting interviews, interview coordination, and completing the new hire on-boarding process.
 Internet navigation/Boolean search skills for sourcing purposes including Social Media experience (including LinkedIn, Facebook, etc.). 
Background working with a startup and/or fast growing company
 Experience working with an ATS system (Lever preferred) and a HRIS system.
 Willingness to recruit aggressively while adhering to ethical business practices. 
Experience managing and prioritizing multiple searches, projects and client relationships all while adhering to compliance guidelines. 
Team player with a high sense of urgency and motivation to see the team succeed. 
Eagerness to grow and learn in the HR and Talent Acquisition profession 
Strong (written and verbal) communication, organization and negotiating skills. 
Self-sufficient and able to work with little direct supervision. 
 
 
